					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13185473#post-4605731</guid>
				<title>Over 200 Billion People?</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13185473/scp-5940#post-4605731</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 20 Apr 2020 15:07:19 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Ruengies_Elaj</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6193532</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I mean, the math works out (7.78 * 1.042^80 = ~209 Billion), but, that'd be an average population density of&#8230; (subtracting water and Antarctica land area, and only half of that is suitable for living)</p> <p>2978 people per square kilometer! (For reference, that's about twice the population density of Malta, the 4th most densely populated country in the world) We already use an area of land greater than Asia to feed (not quite) everyone (technically we make enough food to feed everyone but then our other food eats our food), so how would the world population even be fed?!</p> <p>(Aside from vast quantities of infinite <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-871">cake</a>, <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-1689">potatoes</a>, <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-4503">pasta</a>, <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-458">pizza</a>, <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-109">water</a>&#8230; Okay so we <em>might</em> be able to feed everyone but our stools are going to be rocks.)</p> <p>With that being said, the WTF value was interesting&#8230; No voting for now, may change mind later</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
