					<![CDATA[
						 <p>It's evocative, yes. It has focus and direction, yes. But I don't think it really came to any conclusion. I think a significant part of this is that there is significant detail describing extraction and ritual but the influence of such upon each person isn't known, and undescribed. The initial mystery was laid out in the containment procedures, but the rest of the description doesn't really elaborate upon the mystery in a way that helps conclude or resolve it.</p> 
				 	]]>
